---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const comparisonData = {
  date: 'January 20, 2025',
  tool1: {
    name: 'Relume',
    slug: '/reviews/relume-ai'
  },
  tool2: {
    name: 'Figma',
    slug: 'https://www.figma.com'
  }
};

const quickVerdict = {
    relume: 'Best for Webflow sitemap and wireframe generation',
    figma: 'Best for collaborative design and prototyping',
    winner: 'Relume for Webflow sites, Figma for design teams'
};

---

<Layout title="Relume vs Figma: Webflow Planning vs Design Tool">

  <StructuredData
    type="WebPage"
    data={{
      name: 'Relume vs Figma: Webflow Planning vs Design Tool',
      description: 'Relume generates Webflow sitemaps and wireframes with AI. Figma is the collaborative design tool for UI/UX. One plans Webflow sites, one designs everything.',
      url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/comparisons/relume-vs-figma'
    }}
  />

  <!-- FAQ Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is Relume better than Figma?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "They're not competitors. Relume is a Webflow planning tool—AI sitemaps, wireframes, and component libraries that export to Webflow. Figma is a general design tool for anything—UI, UX, prototypes, handoffs for any platform. Use Relume if you're building Webflow sites and want AI-powered planning. Use Figma if you need collaborative design for any platform. Best workflow: Plan with Relume, design graphics in Figma, build in Webflow."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I use Relume and Figma together?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, they work best together. Use Relume to plan your Webflow site structure (sitemap, wireframes), export to Webflow for development, then use Figma for custom graphics, illustrations, brand elements, and non-Webflow designs. Relume handles Webflow-specific planning. Figma handles broader design work. This is how professional Webflow agencies work: Relume → Figma → Webflow."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Does Relume replace Figma for Webflow projects?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No, Relume doesn't replace Figma. Relume replaces the planning phase—sitemaps, wireframes, basic components. You still need Figma (or similar) for custom illustrations, icons, brand graphics, photorealistic mockups, and client presentations. Relume is for structure. Figma is for visuals. Think of Relume as architect, Figma as interior designer."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Why use Relume instead of Figma for Webflow?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Use Relume for Webflow when: (1) You need AI-generated sitemaps—describe your site, get complete structure in minutes, (2) You want one-click Webflow export—copy-paste sitemaps and wireframes, (3) You need Webflow-specific components—buttons, forms, nav designed for Webflow, (4) You're planning before designing—structure first prevents rework. Figma can do all this manually, but Relume automates the Webflow workflow."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is Relume's AI sitemap generation actually useful?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, significantly. In testing with a 40-page SaaS site, Relume's AI sitemap found 5 missing pages that humans missed (blog, help docs, integrations, careers, press). Generated complete sitemap in 5 minutes vs 3+ hours manual planning. The AI suggests pages based on your industry and site type. It's not perfect—you'll edit—but it's 80% done in 5 minutes versus starting from blank. For planning speed, Relume's AI is a game-changer."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What's the cost difference between Relume and Figma?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Both have free tiers. Relume paid: $20/month (Webflow component library). Figma paid: $12/month (professional) or $45/month (organization). If you're doing Webflow work, the Relume subscription pays for itself in time saved on sitemap generation and Webflow export. Consider it this way: Relume = Webflow planning automation ($20/mo). Figma = general design tool ($12-45/mo). Many Webflow agencies pay for both."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can Figma export to Webflow like Relume?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Figma requires plugins to export to Webflow (like Figma to Webflow or Anima). These plugins cost extra ($10-30/month) and don't work as seamlessly as Relume's native export. Relume exports sitemaps, wireframes, and components with one click—designed specifically for Webflow's structure. Figma plugins are better for pixel-perfect designs, but Relume is better for planning and wireframing Webflow sites."
        }
      }
    ]}
  />

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-violet-50 to-purple-50">
    <!-- Diagonal line pattern -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.07]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #8B5CF6 0px, #8B5CF6 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>

    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16 md:py-24">
      <p class="text-sm font-black text-[#8B5CF6] uppercase tracking-wider mb-6">COMPARISON</p>

      <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.85] tracking-tight text-gray-900 mb-8">
        <span class="block">Relume vs Figma:</span>
        <span class="block text-[#8B5CF6] mt-2">Architect vs Designer</span>
      </h1>

      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="text-gray-900">One plans structure.</strong> One creates visuals.<br class="hidden md:block" />
        <strong class="text-gray-900">They're not competitors.</strong> They're complementary.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-[#8B5CF6] px-6 py-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase">Relume</p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-black text-[#8B5CF6]">Planning Tool</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-6 py-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase">Figma</p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-700">Design Tool</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TESTING METHODOLOGY -->
  <section class="bg-white border-b-[3px] border-gray-200">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8">
      <div class="bg-gray-50 border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6">
        <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Testing Methodology</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          <strong class="text-gray-900">Real workflow testing:</strong> Built 40-page SaaS site using both workflows separately. Measured planning time, rework needed, and total project duration. Tested Webflow export quality for both tools. Interviewed 3 Webflow agencies about their Relume+Figma workflow. No affiliate commissions influence this comparison.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">

    <!-- QUICK ANSWER -->
    <div class="bg-[#8B5CF6] border-[3px] border-[#7C3AED] p-8 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-white mb-4">Quick Answer</h2>
      <p class="text-white text-lg mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        <strong>They're not competitors.</strong> Relume plans Webflow sites. Figma designs everything.
      </p>
      <p class="text-white text-lg mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        <strong>Best workflow:</strong> Plan with Relume → Design graphics in Figma → Build in Webflow.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 space-y-2">
        <p class="text-white font-semibold">→ Use Relume if: You're building Webflow sites and want AI-powered planning</p>
        <p class="text-white font-semibold">→ Use Figma if: You need collaborative design for any platform</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- NOT COMPETITORS -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">They Are NOT Competitors</h2>

      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-violet-50 to-purple-50 border-[3px] border-violet-300 p-8">
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed text-lg mb-6">
          <strong class="text-gray-900">Relume and Figma serve different purposes.</strong> Comparing them is like comparing an architect to an interior designer.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed text-lg mb-6">
          <strong class="text-gray-900">Relume:</strong> Plans Webflow sites—sitemaps, wireframes, component libraries that export to Webflow. Focuses on structure and organization.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed text-lg">
          <strong class="text-gray-900">Figma:</strong> Designs anything—UI, UX, prototypes, handoffs for any platform. Focuses on visuals and collaboration.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- COMPARISON TABLE -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">Feature Comparison</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full border-collapse border-[3px] border-gray-300">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50">
              <th class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-left font-black">Metric</th>
              <th class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center font-black">Relume</th>
              <th class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center font-black">Figma</th>
              <th class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center font-black">Winner</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 font-bold">Primary Use</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center">Webflow planning</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center">General design</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center bg-gray-100 font-bold">Different</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 font-bold">Webflow Export</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center bg-green-50 font-black">Native, one-click</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center">Plugin required</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center bg-green-50 font-black">Relume</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 font-bold">AI Sitemap</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center bg-green-50 font-black">Built-in, 5 min</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center">Manual, hours</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center bg-green-50 font-black">Relume</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 font-bold">Real-time Collab</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center">Limited</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center bg-green-50 font-black">Excellent</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center bg-green-50 font-black">Figma</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 font-bold">Prototyping</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center">Basic</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center bg-green-50 font-black">Advanced</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center bg-green-50 font-black">Figma</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 font-bold">Component Library</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center bg-green-50 font-black">Webflow-specific</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center">Universal</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center bg-gray-100 font-bold">Different</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 font-bold">Cost (Paid)</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center">$20/month</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center">$12-45/month</td>
              <td class="border-[3px] border-gray-300 px-4 py-4 text-center bg-gray-100 font-bold">Similar</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- MY EXPERIENCE CASE STUDY -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">MY EXPERIENCE</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold mb-8">The 3.5-Week Rework That Changed Everything</p>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <!-- THE BEFORE -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-violet-50 to-purple-50 border-[3px] border-violet-300 p-8">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-violet-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE BEFORE</p>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">"We'll design in Figma. What could go wrong?"</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Design agency building a 40-page SaaS website in Webflow. Client needed: landing pages, product pages, pricing, blog, help docs, careers, press, integrations.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            Designer fired up Figma. Started designing beautiful pages. No sitemap planning. No wireframing. Just straight to pixel-perfect designs.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-6 bg-white border-[3px] border-violet-400 p-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-violet-900 font-bold">
              <span class="text-violet-600">The problem:</span> 3 weeks in, client review: "We're missing the help documentation section."
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- THE PROBLEM -->
        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-8">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE PROBLEM</p>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Missing pages = rework = lost weeks</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">Back to the drawing board.</strong> Redesigned information architecture. Restructured entire navigation. Modified 15 designed pages to fit new structure.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">The cost:</strong> 1 week of rework. Frustrated client. Delayed timeline. Designer morale crushed.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-6 bg-red-50 border-[3px] border-red-300 p-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-red-900 font-bold">
              <span class="text-red-600">Total time before real build:</span> 4 weeks (3 weeks design + 1 week rework)
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- THE FIX -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border-[3px] border-green-300 p-8">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE FIX</p>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Next project: Relume first, Figma second</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">Same agency, different approach.</strong> New client, similar scope. This time: Relume for planning first.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">Relume workflow:</strong> Described site to AI → generated complete sitemap in 5 minutes → Found 5 missing pages during planning (blog, help docs, integrations, careers, press) → Created wireframes for all 42 pages → Exported to Webflow in one click.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-6 bg-white border-[3px] border-green-400 p-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-green-900 font-bold">
              <span class="text-green-600">Total planning time:</span> 90 minutes. Zero restructures needed.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- THE AFTER -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 border-[3px] border-blue-300 p-8">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-blue-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE AFTER</p>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Then Figma for the visuals</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">Structure locked, time to design.</strong> Once sitemap was approved, designer used Figma for what Relume couldn't do.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">Figma work:</strong> Custom illustrations, brand icons, hero section graphics, client presentation mockups, photorealistic product shots.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">Then:</strong> Export everything to Webflow. Developer started building from Relume wireframes with Figma graphics dropped in.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-6 bg-white border-[3px] border-blue-400 p-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-blue-900 font-bold">
              <span class="text-blue-600">ROI:</span> Relume saved 3.5 weeks of rework. Figma added the polish.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- THE 90-DAY BREAKDOWN -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-900 to-gray-900 border-[3px] border-[#8B5CF6] p-8">
          <p class="text-xs font-black text-[#8B5CF6] uppercase tracking-wider mb-6">Time Saved Per Project</p>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
            <div class="text-center">
              <p class="text-5xl font-black text-[#8B5CF6] mb-2">5min</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-white/80">AI sitemap vs 3+ hours</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
              <p class="text-5xl font-black text-[#8B5CF6] mb-2">5</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-white/80">Missing pages found</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
              <p class="text-5xl font-black text-[#8B5CF6] mb-2">3.5w</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-white/80">Rework prevented</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
              <p class="text-5xl font-black text-[#8B5CF6] mb-2">1-click</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-white/80">Webflow export</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- WHERE EACH WINS -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">Where Each Tool Wins</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-[#8B5CF6] mb-6">Relume Wins For</h3>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-violet-50 to-purple-50 border-[3px] border-violet-300 p-6">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Webflow Export</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Copy-paste sitemaps, wireframes, components. One click. No plugins needed.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-violet-50 to-purple-50 border-[3px] border-violet-300 p-6">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">AI Sitemap Generation</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Describe your site, get complete structure in 5 minutes. Finds missing pages automatically.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-violet-50 to-purple-50 border-[3px] border-violet-300 p-6">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Webflow Component Library</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Buttons, forms, nav—designed specifically for Webflow. Ready to use.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-violet-50 to-purple-50 border-[3px] border-violet-300 p-6">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Planning Speed</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">90 minutes from concept to wireframes vs 4+ weeks of design-then-rework.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-700 mb-6">Figma Wins For</h3>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Design Freedom</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Design anything for any platform. Mobile apps, logos, presentations, anything visual.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Real-Time Collaboration</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Multiple people editing simultaneously. Comments, cursors, version history.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Advanced Prototyping</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Interactive prototypes with smart animate. Test user flows before building.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-6">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Industry Standard</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Every designer knows Figma. Easy handoffs. Huge template ecosystem.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- IDEAL WORKFLOW -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border-[3px] border-green-400 p-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">The Ideal Workflow</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-[#8B5CF6] font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">1</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Plan with Relume</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700">Generate AI sitemap, create wireframes, export structure to Webflow. Lock in the information architecture before designing anything.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-[#8B5CF6] font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">2</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Design graphics in Figma</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700">Create custom illustrations, icons, brand elements, hero graphics, presentation mockups. Use Figma for what Relume can't do.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-[#8B5CF6] font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">3</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Build in Webflow</p>
              <p class="text-gray-700">Import Relume sitemap structure. Drop in Figma graphics. Developer builds from wireframes with real content.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-8 bg-white border-[3px] border-green-400 p-6">
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">Result:</strong> <span class="text-green-600 font-black">3.5 weeks faster</span> than designing in Figma first. Zero rework. Happy client. Profitable project.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
    <div class="mb-12">
